      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how deeply disappointing it is when people offer clinical explanations for the pain you are feeling, especially when the loss feels so personal and total. You are right that this exhaustion of pretending is a valid reaction to a world that suddenly feels hollow and unresponsive. It is a brave step to admit that you are no longer able to function as you were before, and that feeling like a ghost is a symptom of the intense grief you are carrying.",
